results.reasoning: Extremely rare genetic syndrome with fewer than 20 reported cases worldwide. No systematic epidemiological studies found; estimates based on case report frequency.
Rare hematologic malignancy, estimated ~0.1 per 100k based on case report frequency and limited literature. Fewer than 200 cases reported worldwide in medical literature.

Dental endodontic infections common in populations with access to dental care. Estimated ~50 per 100k based on endodontic treatment frequencies (~0.05-0.1% of population annually require root canal therapy). Geographic variation significant.
results.source: Dental epidemiological estimates based on endodontic treatment frequency

results.reasoning: Rare autosomal recessive congenital muscular dystrophy caused by mutations in COL6A genes. Estimated ~0.05 per 100k births based on rare genetic disorder prevalence. Fewer than 100 confirmed cases in literature.

Rare genetic disorder (MCPH2) caused by mutations in ASPM gene. Estimated ~0.1 per 100k births based on rare genetic disorders in birth defect registries. More common in populations with high consanguinity.

notes: All 5 diseases are rare to extremely rare conditions
Only 1 disease (Root canal infection) has moderate data quality; others have weak data quality
3 of 5 diseases are identified as subtypes with parent disease categories
No verifiable published sources found for genetic/rare disorders - estimates based on case frequency and epidemiological literature
Geographic variation significant for 2 diseases (Root canal infection, MCPH2)
All diseases use incidence metric - appropriate for these acute/congenital conditions
